THAT are these arrayed in white , Brighter than the noonday sun ; Foremost of the sons of light , Nearest the eternal throne ? These are they that bore the cross , Nobly for their Master stood ; Sufferers in his righteous cause , Followers of the dying God . 2 Out of great distress they came , Washed their robes by faith below In the blood of yonder Lamb ,
